    "desc": "Scout tank of the F-series. Scrapped cannons from the aging F10 model was used to save money. To save money and standardize engine across all F-series tanks the tank was required to use the same engine as the F11. However the overall size of the hull was to be much smaller, resulting in a large rear to house the engine.",
